  "local_port": 50076,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "Linking your Aadhaar card to your State Bank of India (SBI) account is a straightforward process and can be done through several convenient methods. Here are the most common ways to link your Aadhaar to SBI:\n\n### 1. **Online via SBI Internet Banking:**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- Active SBI Internet Banking account credentials.\n- Your Aadhaar number.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Log In:** Visit the [SBI Internet Banking Portal](https://www.onlinesbi.com/) and log in using your User ID and password.\n2. **Navigate to Profile Settings:**\n   - Once logged in, click on the **'Profile'** tab located usually at the top right corner.\n3. **Link Aadhaar:**\n   - In the profile settings, find and select the **'Link Aadhaar'** option.\n4. **Enter Details:**\n   - Input your **Aadhaar number** exactly as it appears.\n   - Confirm your mobile number registered with Aadhaar if prompted.\n5. **Submit:**\n   - After verifying the details, submit the information.\n6. **Confirmation:**\n   - You should receive a confirmation message indicating that your Aadhaar has been successfully linked.\n\n### 2. **Through SBI Mobile Banking App:**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- SBI mobile banking app installed on your smartphone.\n- Registered mobile number with SBI and Aadhaar.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Open the App:** Launch the SBI mobile banking app and log in with your credentials.\n2. **Navigate to Profile Settings:**\n   - Tap on the **'Profile'** or **'Manage Profile'** section.\n3. **Link Aadhaar:**\n   - Select the option to **'Link Aadhaar'**.\n4. **Enter Your Aadhaar Number:**\n   - Carefully input your Aadhaar number.\n5. **Verify and Submit:**\n   - Follow the on-screen instructions to verify and submit your Aadhaar details.\n6. **Confirmation:**\n   - A success message will appear once the linking process is complete.\n\n### 3. **Visiting an SBI Branch:**\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Locate a Branch:** Find the nearest SBI branch to your location.\n2. **Prepare Documents:**\n   - Carry a valid **Aadhaar card** and a **recent passport-sized photograph** if required.\n3. **Fill Out a Form:**\n   - Request the **Aadhaar linking form** at the branch and fill it out with accurate details.\n4. **Submit Documents:**\n   - Hand over the completed form along with your Aadhaar card to the bank representative.\n5. **Verification:**\n   - The bank staff will verify your details and process the linking.\n6. **Confirmation:**\n   - You'll receive a confirmation through SMS or email once the process is successfully completed.\n\n### 4. **Using SBI ATM:**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- SBI ATM card.\n- Aadhaar card.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Visit an SBI ATM:** Go to the nearest SBI ATM.\n2. **Insert Your ATM Card:** Enter your PIN to access the ATM menu.\n3. **Select Services:** Look for the **'Aadhaar Linking'** or similar option in the service menu.\n4. **Enter Aadhaar Details:** Input your Aadhaar number when prompted.\n5. **Submit:**\n   - Confirm the details and submit the request.\n6. **Confirmation:**\n   - A receipt or SMS confirmation will be provided once the Aadhaar is linked to your account.\n\n### 5. **Via SMS:**\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n- Registered mobile number with your SBI account and Aadhaar.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Compose SMS:** Draft an SMS in the following format:\n   - `LINK AADHAAR <Your_Aadhaar_Number>`\n   - *Example:* `LINK AADHAAR 123456789012`\n2. **Send SMS:** Send this SMS to the designated SBI number (usually 57575 or as specified by SBI).\n3. **Confirmation:** You should receive an SMS confirming the linkage of your Aadhaar to your SBI account.\n\n### **Important Points to Note:**\n\n- **Accuracy:** Ensure that all details entered, especially your Aadhaar number and mobile number, are accurate to avoid any issues during the linking process.\n  \n- **One Aadhaar Rule:** As per Indian regulations, each individual can have only one Aadhaar linked to their bank accounts. Ensure that your Aadhaar isn't already linked to another SBI account.\n\n- **KYC Compliance:** Linking Aadhaar fulfills the KYC (Know Your Customer) norms required by banks, ensuring smoother access to various banking services.\n\n- **Security:** Always ensure that your Aadhaar details are entered on official SBI platforms or directly with bank representatives to protect your personal information.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or need further assistance, it's advisable to contact SBI's customer support or visit your nearest SBI branch for personalized help.",
